3- There is a bug in the navigation behavior:

When I am on the homepage and I hover over the PRODUCTION section in the navbar, then select one of the following items: Publications, Communications, or Thèses, I am redirected to the production page.

{
  title: 'PRODUCTION',
  sections: [
    {
      label: 'Scientifique',
      links: [
        { label: 'Publications', route: '/production/LaRESI' },
        { label: 'Communications', route: '/production/LaRESI', fragment: 'communications' },
        { label: 'Thèses', route: '/production/LaRESI', fragment: 'theses' }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

On the production page, the corresponding tab is automatically selected, which is expected.

However, the issue appears when I try to change the selection:

If I click another item from the navbar, the tabs update correctly.
But if I try to change the selection directly using the tabs component, the selection becomes stuck on the last navbar-selected item.

Tabs definition:

protected readonly tabs: readonly TabItem[] = [
  { id: 'publications', label: 'Publications' },
  { id: 'communications', label: 'Communications' },
  { id: 'theses', label: 'Thèses' }
];

Template:

<app-tabs 
  [tabs]="tabs" 
  [activeId]="activeTab()" 
  (tabChange)="selectTab($event)" 
/>

Expected behavior:

Navbar selection and tabs should stay synchronized
Tabs should remain independently clickable after navigation
No “locking” on the last navbar-selected tab

Actual behavior:

Tab selection gets stuck on the last navbar interaction



